vdrdevel (1.3.12-3) unstable; urgency=low

  * Extracted code for handling remote.conf's from vdr.init to
    remotes-loader.sh.
  * Added new package vdrdevel-dbg, which installs a debuggable vdr as
    /usr/bin/vdrdevel-dbg as well as some helper scripts.
  * Adapted patches for new dpatch >= 2.0.9.
  * vdrdevel-dev now installs /usr/bin/vdrdeveldbg-buildpackage, which allows
    to build debuggable plugins

 -- Tobias Grimm <tg@e-tobi.net>  Tue, 20 Oct 2004 00:05:00 +0200

vdrdevel (1.3.12-2) unstable; urgency=low

  * Thomas Günther <tom@toms-cafe.de>:
    - Adapted to new FHS-conform directory structure
    - Took over changes from vdr 1.2.6-27
    - Installing channels.conf and examples into config dir in postinst
    - Copying of remote conf files from vdr-1.2.6 in init script
  * Tobias Grimm <tg@e-tobi.net>:
    - moved /usr/bin/vdr-recordingaction to /usr/lib/vdr/vdr-recordingaction
    - moved /usr/bin/shutdownvdr to /usr/lib/vdr/vdr-shutdown
    - default location for recordings according to FHS is now /var/lib/video
    - The vdr config dir is /var/lib/vdr now. Real config files are linked to
      this directory, while generated or vdr-managed config files 
      (like timers.conf) can exist physically in this directory.
    - Shutdown-Hook mechanism taken over from Alioth. Hook scripts are no
      longer  restricted to be shell scripts. (See README.Debian)
    - moved PLUGIN_DIR, PLUGIN_PREFIX, CFG_DIR, PLUGIN_CFG_DIR,
      PLUGIN_ORDER_FILE, CMDHOOKSDIR, REC_CMD and SHUTDOWN_CMD from the
      default file to the init script
    - renamed /usr/bin/ctvdr*.sh to /usr/bin/ctvdr*
    - using debian/compat now
    - took over order.commands.conf, order.reccmds.conf and order.conf
      from Alioth
    - renamed vdraptrefresh.sh to vdraptrefresh
    - all strings in vdr.menu are now quoted
    - added manpage for runvdr
    - moved poweroffvdr to /usr/bin/
    - reduced vdr.dirs to /usr/lib/vdr/plugins/
    - moved epg2html.pl and svdrpsend.pl to /usr/lib/vdr/
    - Linking var/lib/video to var/lib/video.00. This way, adding
      more partitions is simply a matter of creating video.01, video.02 and
      so on.
    - Added workaround for "Video data stream broken" bug, if you use more
      than one DVB card. Just set VDSB_WORKAROUND=yes in /etc/default/vdr to
      enable it. (szap from package dvb-utils is needed!)

 -- Thomas Günther <tom@toms-cafe.de>  Tue,  5 Oct 2004 23:57:01 +0200

vdrdevel (1.3.12-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Tobias Grimm <tg@e-tobi.net>
    - New upstream release
    - took over some changes from the vdr 1.2.6 package
    - removed libncurses dependency, which is only required when compiling with
      DEBUG_OSD
  * Thomas Günther <tom@toms-cafe.de>
    - Took over all changes from vdr-1.2.6-26
    - Using dh_install now completely
    - Using 95_vdrdevel.dpatch for converting vdr -> vdrdevel
    - Extracted patchlevel code to patchlevel.sh
    - Installing patchlevel.sh into vdrdevel-dev package
    - Assembled vdrdevelstart and vdrstandardstart to vdr-switch.sh,
      rebuilt commands.vdrdevel.conf as commands.switch.conf and
      commands.vdrdevel.conf as commands.switch-back.conf
    - Took over patches and patch naming scheme from alioth
    - Renamed recordingaction to vdr-recordingaction (adapted to alioth)
    - Renamed shutdown90.custom.sh to S90.custom (adapted to alioth)
    - Added debian/watch file for uscan
    - Adapted ctvdrinfo.sh to patchlevel in custom control field
    - Corrected package description
    - Added vdr-dev dependency to debhelper
    - Added debconf question to start vdrdevel automatically instead of vdr
    - Added optional patches:
      opt-20_enAIO-1.3-1.3.11
      opt-24_jumpplay-0.5-1.3.12
      opt-25-x_disable-service-provider-1.3.12
      opt-26-x_replay-1.3.11
    - Disabled PLUGIN_CHECK_STARTABLE because of text2skin plugin (segfault)

